commit.message: Release django-autoslug 1.9.6

Handle timezones for datetime fields

* Properly handle timezones for datetime fields
* Add pytz as an optional dependency
Add tag prefix setting for AutoPub
Release django-autoslug 1.9.5

Add license to sdist and wheels (#56)

Add license to sdist and wheels. Also adds run_tests.py to sdist.

Closes https://github.com/justinmayer/django-autoslug/issues/55

Limit before_deploy & deploy stages to Python 3.7

AutoPub currently only runs on Python 3.6+, and we only want it to run
once per build, so this should limit the `before_deploy` and `deploy`
stages (using appropriate Travis syntax for each) to Python 3.7 only.

Contributors will henceforth be asked to include a `RELEASE.md` file
containing the release type (major, minor, patch) and a summary of the
changes in the pull request. This information will be used by the
continuous integration (CI) system to automatically publish a new
release to PyPI when the pull request is merged.
